    <h2>Reporting Vulnerabilities</h2>
    <p>If you believe you found a security vulnerability in HelloDeploy, email <strong>hensonsagorsor@gmail.com</strong> with a clear description, affected URL or component, reproduction steps, impact, and any safe proof of concept.</p>

    <h2>Safe Testing Rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Test only accounts, projects, repositories, and applications you own or are authorized to test.</li>
      <li>Do not access, modify, delete, or exfiltrate another user&rsquo;s data.</li>
      <li>Do not run denial-of-service, resource exhaustion, spam, phishing, malware, or social engineering tests.</li>
      <li>Do not publicly disclose a vulnerability before HelloDeploy has had a reasonable opportunity to investigate and remediate it.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Platform Security Controls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Argon2id password hashing.</li>
      <li>HTTP-only, secure, same-site session cookies.</li>
      <li>CSRF protection and rate limiting.</li>
      <li>Encrypted environment secret values at rest.</li>
      <li>Signed GitHub webhook verification.</li>
      <li>Sanitized deployment logs and token redaction.</li>
      <li>Restricted container execution and resource controls.</li>
      <li>Audit logs for privileged actions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Security Response</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy will review reports, prioritize confirmed issues based on severity, and communicate remediation status where practical. Reports made in good faith under these rules will not be treated as Acceptable Use Policy violations.</p>
  </div>
</div>
